# Pre-built binary (ratchet.exe) IS committed on purpose so downloaders can run
# the host immediately via the launchers - do NOT ignore *.exe here.

# Runtime / dev cruft
*.pdb
_*

# Per-instance runtime, all regenerated - never commit these (they appear inside instances/examples):
#   .index/  the BM25 / embedding search cache (KbIndex)
#   runs/    per-chain-run state (runs/<id>/step-NNN.json)
.index/
runs/

# Per-session memory (written by the chat; not source).
NOTES.md

# OS / editor
Thumbs.db
.DS_Store
*.user
.vs/
PLANS.md
.claude/

# Cross-compiled binaries under bins/<os>-<arch>/ ARE committed on purpose, so anyone who clones can
# run the host immediately for their platform (bins/csharp/ holds the legacy C# build). Do NOT ignore
# them here. Only ignore stray Go build/test artifacts left at the repo root or in package dirs:
/ratchet
/ratchet.test
*.test
*.out